criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All patients who undergo DP whether made by open or laparoscopic surgery;

          -  Patients age 18 to 75 years;

          -  Patients benefit from distal pancreatectomy according to NCCN guidelines;

          -  The subject understands the nature of this trial and willing to comply, and ability to
             provide written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Distant metastases: peritoneal carcinomatosis, liver metastases, distant lymph node
             metastases, involvement of other organs;

          -  History of abdominal disease or surgery which may results in obvious omentum adhesion;

          -  Synchronous malignancy in other organs;

          -  Patients with high operative risk as defined by the American Society of
             Anesthesiologists (ASA) score >4;

          -  Pregnant women.
